{/* ============================================================================
   COASTAL RISK MAP SECTION - Add this right after your Hero section
   ============================================================================ */}
<AnimatedSection>
  <div style={S.storyHeader}>
    <div style={S.storyTitle}>🗺️ The Vanishing Coastline</div>
    <div style={S.storySubtitle}>
      For Pacific island nations, the front line of climate change is their own shoreline. 
      Analysis of Landsat satellite imagery reveals coastlines are retreating at alarming rates.
    </div>
    <div style={S.storyInsight}>💡 Every meter of coastline lost threatens homes, roads, freshwater sources, and cultural heritage</div>
  </div>
  
  <div style={S.chartPanel}>
    {/* Erosion Visualization Map */}
    <div className="relative bg-gradient-to-b from-sky-100 to-blue-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg">
      
      {/* Map Header */}
      <div className="bg-slate-800 px-4 py-2 flex justify-between items-center">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span className="text-yellow-400 text-sm">🗺️</span>
          <span className="text-white text-xs font-medium">Landsat Satellite Analysis | 1990 - 2025</span>
        </div>
        <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span className="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500 animate-pulse"></span>
          <span className="text-white/60 text-[10px]">Live Data</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      {/* Map Container */}
      <div className="relative p-4">
        {/* Decorative Ocean Pattern */}
        <div className="absolute inset-0 opacity-5 pointer-events-none">
          <div className="absolute top-10 left-10 text-4xl">🌊</div>
          <div className="absolute bottom-20 right-20 text-4xl">🌊</div>
          <div className="absolute top-1/2 left-1/3 text-3xl">🌊</div>
        </div>
        
        {/* Placeholder Map - Replace with your actual map image */}
        <div className="relative bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-800 to-emerald-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-inner">
          
          {/* Island Silhouette */}
          <svg viewBox="0 0 800 500" className="w-full h-auto">
            <defs>
              <linearGradient id="oceanGrad" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="0%" y2="100%">
                <stop offset="0%" stopColor="#0ea5e9" />
                <stop offset="100%" stopColor="#0369a1" />
              </linearGradient>
              <linearGradient id="landGrad" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
                <stop offset="0%" stopColor="#22c55e" />
                <stop offset="100%" stopColor="#166534" />
              </linearGradient>
              <filter id="shadow" x="-10%" y="-10%" width="120%" height="120%">
                <feDropShadow dx="0" dy="2" stdDeviation="4" floodOpacity="0.3"/>
              </filter>
            </defs>
            
            {/* Ocean Background */}
            <rect width="800" height="500" fill="url(#oceanGrad)" />
            
            {/* Island Land Mass */}
            <path d="M300,250 Q320,200 380,180 Q420,160 460,170 Q500,180 520,220 Q540,260 530,300 Q520,340 480,360 Q440,380 400,370 Q360,360 340,330 Q320,300 300,250 Z" 
                  fill="url(#landGrad)" filter="url(#shadow)" />
            
            {/* Coastal Erosion Indicators (Red Lines) */}
            <path d="M340,280 L360,275" stroke="#ef4444" strokeWidth="3" strokeLinecap="round" />
            <path d="M380,190 L395,185" stroke="#ef4444" strokeWidth="3" strokeLinecap="round" />
            <path d="M500,280 L515,285" stroke="#ef4444" strokeWidth="3" strokeLinecap="round" />
            <path d="M460,350 L475,355" stroke="#ef4444" strokeWidth="3" strokeLinecap="round" />
            
            {/* Erosion Markers */}
            <g transform="translate(320, 260)">
              <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="15" fill="#ef4444" fillOpacity="0.3" stroke="#ef4444" strokeWidth="2" />
              <text x="0" y="-20" textAnchor="middle" fill="#ef4444" fontSize="10" fontWeight="bold">-4.2m/year</text>
            </g>
            
            <g transform="translate(490, 270)">
              <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="12" fill="#ef4444" fillOpacity="0.3" stroke="#ef4444" strokeWidth="2" />
              <text x="0" y="-18" textAnchor="middle" fill="#ef4444" fontSize="9" fontWeight="bold">-3.8m/year</text>
            </g>
            
            <g transform="translate(430, 340)">
              <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="10" fill="#ef4444" fillOpacity="0.3" stroke="#ef4444" strokeWidth="2" />
              <text x="0" y="-15" textAnchor="middle" fill="#ef4444" fontSize="8" fontWeight="bold">-2.9m/year</text>
            </g>
            
            {/* Stable Coastline Indicators (Green) */}
            <path d="M420,165 L435,160" stroke="#22c55e" strokeWidth="3" strokeLinecap="round" />
            <path d="M270,290 L285,295" stroke="#22c55e" strokeWidth="3" strokeLinecap="round" />
            
            <g transform="translate(430, 155)">
              <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="8" fill="#22c55e" fillOpacity="0.3" stroke="#22c55e" strokeWidth="2" />
              <text x="0" y="-12" textAnchor="middle" fill="#22c55e" fontSize="8" fontWeight="bold">Stable</text>
            </g>
            
            {/* Add a small village icon to show what's at risk */}
            <g transform="translate(410, 310)">
              <rect x="-8" y="-6" width="16" height="12" fill="#fef3c7" rx="1" />
              <polygon points="-10,-6 0,-14 10,-6" fill="#f59e0b" />
              <text x="12" y="-2" fill="#fef3c7" fontSize="8">Village</text>
            </g>
            
            {/* Coral Reef */}
            <path d="M200,320 Q220,340 250,335 Q280,330 300,345" stroke="#60a5fa" strokeWidth="2" fill="none" strokeDasharray="4 4" opacity="0.6"/>
            <text x="250" y="360" fill="#60a5fa" fontSize="9" textAnchor="middle" opacity="0.6">Coral Reef</text>
          </svg>
          
          {/* Legend Overlay */}
          <div className="absolute bottom-4 left-4 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-lg p-2 shadow-md">
            <div className="text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-1">Coastal Change Rate</div>
            <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div className="flex items-center gap-1">
                <div className="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-rose-500"></div>
                <span className="text-[9px] text-slate-600">Erosion (>2m/yr)</span>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-center gap-1">
                <div className="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-emerald-500"></div>
                <span className="text-[9px] text-slate-600">Stable</span>
              </div>
              <div className="flex items-center gap-1">
                <div className="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-amber-500"></div>
                <span className="text-[9px] text-slate-600">At-risk community</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        {/* Instructions for replacing with real data */}
        <div className="mt-3 text-center">
          <p className="text-[10px] text-slate-400 italic">
            🗺️ *This is a representative visualization. Replace with actual Landsat-derived coastal change map for your selected country.*
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      {/* Data Source Footer */}
      <div className="bg-slate-100 px-4 py-2 rounded-b-xl">
        <div className="flex flex-wrap justify-between items-center gap-2 text-[10px] text-slate-500">
          <span>📡 Data Source: Landsat Satellite Imagery (1990-2025)</span>
          <span>📊 Analysis: Digital Earth Pacific Coastlines</span>
          <span>🔬 Method: Multi-temporal shoreline extraction</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    {/* Narrative Context */}
    <div style={S.narrativeText} className="mt-4">
      📖 <span className="font-semibold">What the data tells us:</span> Analysis of three decades of Landsat satellite imagery reveals that Pacific coastlines are not static. 
      In vulnerable areas, shorelines are retreating at rates of <span className="font-bold text-rose-600">3-5 meters per year</span>, threatening roads, homes, freshwater lenses, 
      and culturally significant sites. For low-lying atolls like Tuvalu and Kiribati, coastal erosion is not just an environmental issue—it is an existential threat.
    </div>
    
    {/* Supporting Statistics Card */}
    <div className="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
      <div className="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-white rounded-lg p-3 border border-rose-200">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span className="text-xl">📉</span>
          <span className="text-xs font-semibold text-rose-700">Coastal Retreat</span>
        </div>
        <div className="text-2xl font-bold text-rose-600">3-5m</div>
        <div className="text-[10px] text-slate-500">annual erosion rate in hotspots</div>
      </div>
      
      <div className="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-white rounded-lg p-3 border border-amber-200">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span className="text-xl">🏠</span>
          <span className="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700">Infrastructure Risk</span>
        </div>
        <div className="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-600">70%</div>
        <div className="text-[10px] text-slate-500">of coastal roads & buildings within 100m</div>
      </div>
      
      <div className="bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-50 to-white rounded-lg p-3 border border-cyan-200">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <span className="text-xl">💧</span>
          <span className="text-xs font-semibold text-cyan-700">Freshwater Threat</span>
        </div>
        <div className="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-600">Saltwater</div>
        <div className="text-[10px] text-slate-500">intrusion into freshwater lenses</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</AnimatedSection>